children.name: LOV
children.label: List of values
children.description: Finite, governed set of atomic, typed values (LOV) used to constrain and normalize the range of data properties; codes are stable while labels may be multilingual and versioned.
children.useCase:
The LOV "AcknowledgeResponseType" comprises a closed list of values: "AbleToComply" and "UnableToComply". This enumerations is represented as a owl Class, subclass of  LOV. The two values are represented as indiviuals of the class AcknoledgeResponseType.


:LOV_AcknowledgeResponseType rdf:type owl:Class ;
   rdfs:subClassOf :LOV .

LOV_AcknowledgeResponseType_AbleToComply rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual , :LOV_AcknowledgeResponseType .

LOV_AcknowledgeResponseType_UnableToComply rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual , :LOV_AcknowledgeResponseType .

children.name: Capability
children.label: Capability
children.description: The potential ability to do work, perform a function or mission, achieve an objective, or provide a service.

children.name: Cyber capability
children.label: Cyber capability
children.description: A capability whose primary environment of employment is cyberspace, integrating people, processes, and technical means to plan, execute, sustain, or protect operations and effects on information systems and networks in accordance with doctrine and ROE.

children.name: Comms
children.description: The ability to generate, transmit, route, and receive information/signals to provide connectivity and assured communications (voice/data/video, networking, spectrum management). Moves information.
children.label: Comms

children.name: Cyber
children.description: The ability to create, defend, exploit, or deliver effects within information systems and networks (cyberspace), including DODIN ops, defensive cyber ops, and authorized offensive cyber effects. Acts in the digital substrate.
children.label: Cyber

children.name: Kinetic
children.description: The ability to produce physical effects through mechanical/chemical/explosive energy on material targets (e.g., fires, mobility, breaching, physical destruction). Changes the physical world.
children.label: Kinetic

children.name: Sensor
children.description: The ability to detect, measure, or observe phenomena (physical or logical) and produce observations for awareness/targeting (e.g., EO/IR, radar, SIGINT, cyber telemetry). Creates information.
children.label: Sensor

children.name: Warfare Function
children.label: Warfare function
children.description: Doctrinal set of operational purposes that group and articulate activities and capabilities (e.g., C2, Intelligence, Manoeuvre, Fires, Information, Civil-Military Cooperation, Sustainment, and Force Protection) enabling commanders and staffs to visualize, integrate, and synchronize operations across all domains.

children.name: Command and Control (C2)
children.label: Command and Control (C2)
children.description: Directs and coordinates forces and operations to achieve objectives; enables planning, direction, and synchronization across all domains.

children.name: Civil-Military Cooperation (CIMIC)
children.label: Civil-Military Cooperation (CIMIC)
children.description: Coordinates and facilitates interaction with civil actors, populations, and authorities to support the mission and unity of effort.

children.name: Fires
children.label: Fires
children.description: Delivers effects against targets to degrade, deny, disrupt, or destroy enemy capabilities and will.

children.name: Force Protection
children.label: Force Protection
children.description: Preserves the forces fighting potential by preventing or mitigating hostile actions, hazards, and vulnerabilities.

children.name: Information
children.label: Information
children.description: Creates, protects, senses, and employs information and related capabilities to achieve advantage and influence outcomes.

children.name: Intelligence
children.label: Intelligence
children.description: Collects, analyzes, and disseminates information on the operational environment, threats, and targets to support decision-making.

children.name: Manoeuvre
children.label: Manoeuvre
children.description: Positions and moves forces to gain positional advantage and create favorable conditions for success.

children.name: Sustainment
children.label: Sustainment
children.description: Provides logistics, medical, personnel, and other support to maintain combat power and freedom of action over time.

children.name: Armoured personnel carrier
children.label: Armoured personnel carrier
children.description: A lightly armoured, highly mobile vehicle used primarily for transporting personnel and their individual equipment during tactical operations.

children.name: Assault gun
children.label: Assault gun
children.description: A cannon, with a relatively long barrel, operating with a relatively low angle of fire, and having a high muzzle velocity.

children.name: Cannon
children.label: Cannon
children.description: A weapon for firing projectiles, having a heavy metal tube installed on a carriage or mounting.

children.name: CyberC2
children.label: Cyber C2
children.description: Ability to plan, direct, coordinate, and monitor cyber operations (DODIN ops, DCO, OCO), ensuring commanders intent, battlespace management, and ROE compliance across all echelons.

children.name: CyberSupportCoordination
children.label: Cyber support coordination
children.description: Ability to orchestrate and synchronize cyber-related support across units and stakeholders (tasking, deconfliction, liaison with CSIRTs/ISPs/coalition), integrating cyber into joint planning and sustainment.

children.name: CyberDefensive
children.label: Cyber defensive
children.description: Ability to prevent, detect, respond to, and recover from cyber threats to preserve mission assurance (hardening, monitoring, incident response, and continuity of operations).

children.name: CyberForceProtection
children.label: Cyber force protection
children.description: Ability to protect personnel, platforms, and mission systems from cyber effects across the mission lifecycle (endpoint security, mission assurance, COMSEC, digital OPSEC).

children.name: CyberISR
children.label: Cyber ISR
children.description: Ability to collect, process, analyze, and disseminate intelligence about the cyber environment and adversary activity (asset discovery, enumeration, traffic analysis, threat intel).

children.name: CyberOffensive
children.label: Cyber offensive
children.description: Ability to deliver authorized cyber effects (degrade, deny, disrupt, deceive, destroy) against targets to achieve operational objectives in accordance with law, policy, and ROE.

children.name: Surveillance
children.label: Surveillance capability
children.description: A Capability, required for planning, of those Facilities, Equipment, Organisations and Persons that are deemed as having the nominal ability to observe aerospace, surface or subsurface areas, places, persons, or things, by visual, aural, electronic, photographic or other means.

children.name: Infantry Unit
children.label: Infantry unit
children.description: A CombatUnit whose principal designation is the employment of non-mechanised or lorry-(truck-)borne infantry.

children.name: Information warfare unit
children.label: Information warfare unit
children.description: A Unit whose principal designation is to achieve information superiority.

children.description: Classifies victims by priority order to assist and stabilise them

children.label: BasicTriageSHORT
children.description: First Triage. Done at Rescue Area
